<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 20 at 3:46PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHERN SURRY...NORTHEASTERN
WILKES AND YADKIN COUNTIES THROUGH 445 PM EDT...
At 345 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dockery, or near Traphill, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.
Locations impacted include...
North Wilkesboro...
Elkin...
Fairview...
Yadkinville...
Jonesville...
Dobson...
and Pilot Mountain.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Seek shelter inside a building.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
